OL,6,F"They have to understand stalking is
OL,7,Faround a pattern of behaviour, it's
OL,8,Fobsessive, it's frequent, it's
OL,9,Funwanted. If they're responding to
OL,10,Findividual incidents and not putting
OL,11,Fthose patterns together then it may
OL,12,Fnot be recognised as stalking.
OL,14,F"Stalking is incredibly dangerous. In
OL,15,Fmany domestic homicides stalking has
