OL,4,Cprotection orders
OL,6,FThey are not an alternative to
OL,7,Fprosecution, but can be used to
OL,8,Fcomplement the prosecution of a
OL,9,Fstalking offence.
OL,11,FOnce granted, a SPO can ban the
OL,12,Fdefendant from behaving in certain
OL,13,Fways and require them to meet certain
OL,14,Frules.
OL,16,FThere is no specific legal definition
OL,17,Fof stalking.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/21
